job.job_description:
&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Figma is growing our team of passionate creatives and builders on a mission to make design accessible to all. Figma’s platform helps teams bring ideas to life—whether you&#39;re brainstorming, creating a prototype, translating designs into code, or iterating with AI. From idea to product, Figma empowers teams to streamline workflows, move faster, and work together in real time from anywhere in the world. If you&#39;re excited to shape the future of design and collaboration, join us!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Product Manager to join our Communication Tools pillar who will help us shape the future of content and digital asset management systems. You’ll extend Figma’s existing ecosystem to natively manage the content, assets, and components of any digital product in production. You’ll collaborate heavily with many teams across Figma including the Editor, Infrastructure, Build Tools, Growth + Monetization teams, and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role that can be held from one of our US hubs or remotely in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you’ll do at Figma:&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Combine your experience with design systems, technical expertise, and empathy for teams who rely daily on CMS / DAM products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product, design, and engineering leadership to define, sharpen, and execute the long-term strategy of Figma’s future CMS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align your team around solutions to complex infrastructure-related product requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace and push the world of open source software forward as we deliver engineering teams tools that fit their workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the core Figma Editor team in order to connect dynamic content to existing Figma product surfaces in new ways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex technical concepts for non-technical stakeholders and communicate the value of foundational improvements across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
