&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CI/CD is the beating heart of Vercel&lt;/strong&gt;. Whether you’re previewing a new idea from v0 or shipping the next great thing to production, every customer builds — and &lt;strong&gt;millions of builds flow through our systems every day&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Software Engineer on the CI/CD team, you&#39;ll work on the infrastructure that powers these builds at scale. You&#39;ll improve performance, enhance reliability, and evolve the systems that developers rely on to deliver fast, iterative workflows. This role blends product thinking with deep systems work — you&#39;ll be building features that serve both internal teams and Vercel&#39;s global developer community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for engineers who are excited to work on high-scale systems, love improving the developer experience, and want to have a direct impact on how software gets shipped on the web.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re based within a pre-determined commuting distance of one of our offices (SF, NY, London, or Berlin), the role includes in-office anchor days on Monday, Tuesday, and Friday. If you&#39;re located beyond that distance, the role is fully remote. For location-specific details, please connect with our recruiting team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build high-performance microservices that power the entire deployment lifecycle—from handling webhooks to designing database schemas and building scalable APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in an on-call rotation for the Vercel build pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve the Deployments user interface.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities and lead projects to enhance performance, reliability, and developer experience of CI/CD on Vercel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve the developer experience for both small projects and large monorepos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of industry trends and advancements in CI/CD technologies, bringing innovative ideas to the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with the open-source community, participate in discussions, and contribute to related projects, aligning with Vercel&#39;s commitment to giving back to the developer community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clean, efficient, tested, and well-documented code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About You:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience building full-stack applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience designing and maintaining APIs and distributed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience building intuitive user interfaces using modern frontend frameworks like React or Svelte.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong proficiency in JavaScript/TypeScript and experience with modern frontend development tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent communication skills and the ability to work effectively in a collaborative team environment, and are eager to learn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have opinions about how to architect scalable codebases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Bonus If You:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are a React or Next.js expert.&lt;/li&gt;
